dji.sdk.api.Gimbal

Class DJIInspireGimbal

  • java.lang.Object
    • dji.sdk.api.DJIObject
      • dji.sdk.api.Gimbal.DJIGimbal
        • dji.sdk.api.Gimbal.DJIInspireGimbal

  • public class DJIInspireGimbal
extends DJIGimbal

    Dji Inspire Gimbal Class TODO

    DJIInspireGimbalClass is a specific class for Inspire 1 and Phantom 3. Inheriting from the base class, DJIGimbalClass, DJIInspireGimbalClass could be used to control the Gimbal of Inspire 1 and Phantom 3.

    However, please remember that pitch is the only direction that could be changed for Phantom 3.
    Version:
    : V2.4.0
    Author:
    : DJI Software

      • startUpdateTimer

        public boolean startUpdateTimer(int interval)
        Start upating timer and set the interval between each update.his function will set up an updating timer for updating the status of the Gimbal. This timer will periodically request information of gimal's attribute, errors (if it exists) and calibration status. Developer could use setGimbalUpdateAttitudeCallBack, set GimbalErrorCallBack and setDJIGimbalCalibrationStatusCallBack to design the action while the sdk receives the information.
        Please Note that the interval could not be lower than 100;
        Overrides:
        startUpdateTimer in class DJIGimbal
        Parameters:
        interval - The interval between each updating Timer. This will effect the frequency of transporting information from the aircraft. In addition for Inspire1 the minimum of the interval is 100ms.
        Returns:
        boolean true for successfully starting Update timer.
            false for informing failure.
        See Also:
        DJIGimbal.startUpdateTimer(int), DJIGimbalAttitude, DJIGimbalCalibrationStatus, setGimbalUpdateAttitudeCallBack(DJIGimbalUpdateAttitudeCallBack), setGimbalErrorCallBack(DJIGimbalErrorCallBack), setDJIGimbalCalibrationStatusCallBack(DJIGimbalCalibrationStatusCallBack)

        public void resetGimbalSpeedConfig(dji.midware.interfaces.DJIDataCallBack mCallBack)
        By invoking this function, both velocity of each direction and gimbal mode will be reset to the default configuration.
        Parameters:
        velocity - The range of the velocity is [-1000, 1000]. The higher absolute value of the velocity is, the faster the gimbal will roll.
        mCallBack - DJIDataCallBack is an interface with two function without development
          onScucess() - With this function, you could design what the app will do if the function executes correctly.
          onFailure() - With this function, you could design what the app will do if the function executes incorrectlyã€‚

        public int setGimbalFpvMode(boolean isFpv)
        Set gimbal follow mode.
        Set up first personal vision (FPV). Once you set up this vision, you could get the FPV of the aircraft and the gimbal will not maintain its front-facing angle until you set it back.

         true - the module will be set to FPV.

      • updateGimbalAttitude

        public void updateGimbalAttitude(DJIGimbalRotation pitch,
                                 DJIGimbalRotation roll,
                                 DJIGimbalRotation yaw)
        Update the gimbal angle. Please notice that the parameters are objects of DJIGimbalRotation and please make sure that the parameters (enable, direction, type, angle) are set correctly. Inspire 1 supports setting the angle of pitch, roll, yaw. Phantom 3 just supports setting the angle of pitch, and the tuning of roll.
        Overrides:
        updateGimbalAttitude in class DJIGimbal
        Parameters:
        pitch - The pitch angle (DJIGimbalRotation object)
        roll - The roll angle (DJIGimbalRotation object)
        yaw - The yaw angle (DJIGimbalROtation object)
